| עַל           | On, upon        |
| בְּ           | In, on, at      |
| כָּל          | All, every      |

---

## Grammar

- Use of הִנֵּה as presentative ("Behold!"/"Here is X!")
- Narrative waw-consecutive for simple past action in Qal (esp. "וַיִּרְדְּפוּ", "וַיִּנְפֹּל"—though employed in simplified form for early beginners)
- Animal sound onomatopoeia
- Roots repeated in related forms (e.g., ר.צ.ה in different conjugations: רָץ, רָצָה, רָצוּ)
- Simple subject-verb agreement (singular/plural/gendered)
- Repetition of nouns and contrasting adjectives (big/small, afraid/happy)
- Qal perfect forms for narrative sequencing
- Simple word order focusing on VSO (verb-subject-object), as is typical in Biblical Hebrew narrative

**Minimized introduction of new grammar. Focus is on action verbs, animal forms, and sequencing through "and"/ו and "then"/ו, and the simple presentative "הִנֵּה".**
